olive oil
20 g butter
1.5 cup water
1 packet basmati rice
1 bag baby broccoli
2 leaves makrut lime leaves
½ lemon
1 packet beef strips
1 packet Ginger & Lemongrass Paste
1 tin coconut milk
2 tbs soy sauce
½ tbs brown sugar
1 packet roasted peanuts
3 clove garlic
1 bag Asian Greens

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, heat the butter with a dash of olive oil over a medium heat.
• Cook 1/2 the garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Add the water, basmati rice and a generous pinch of salt, stir, then bring to the boil. Reduce heat to low and cover with a lid. Cook for 10 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, trim and halve baby broccoli. Roughly chop Asian greens. Remove centre veins from makrut lime leaves, then very finely chop. Slice lemon into wedges.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a high heat. When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a plate.

TIP: The makrut lime leaves are fibrous so you want to finely chop them!

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender

• Return the frying pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook baby broccoli until just tender, 3-4 minutes.
• Add ginger & lemongrass paste, makrut lime and remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add coconut milk, the soy sauce and the brown sugar. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until slightly reduced, 3-4 minutes.
• Stir Asian greens through sauce and cook until just wilted, 1-2 minutes. Add a squeeze of lemon juice, then return beef (plus any resting juices) to the pan and stir to combine.

• Divide garlic rice between bowls, then top with ginger and coconut beef.
• Garnish with roasted peanuts and serve with any remaining lemon wedges.